# ComfyUI

## What this layer does

`ComfyUI` provides a browser-based video workflow surface exposed through the dedicated `ai-video` layer.

This layer preinstalls two local video generation families:

- `${COMFYUI_LTX_MODEL_TITLE}`
- `${COMFYUI_WAN_MODEL_TITLE}`

The runtime itself is pinned to `${COMFYUI_REPO}` at revision `${COMFYUI_REVISION}`.

## How to access it

- Browser URL: `${COMFYUI_URL}`
- Gateway username: `${COMFYUI_GATEWAY_USER}`
- Gateway password: `${COMFYUI_GATEWAY_PASSWORD}`

## Runtime notes

- The service is published only when the `ai-video` layer is enabled.
- Model files are stored inside a persistent Docker volume mounted at `ComfyUI/models`.
- The managed video model set is defined in `config/models/comfyui-models.json`.
- `LTX-Video` is staged with its `T5 XXL` text encoder.
- `Wan 2.1 1.3B` is staged with its `UMT5` text encoder and `VAE`.

## Typical workflow

1. Start the lab with `atlas-lab up --with-ai-video`
2. Open `${COMFYUI_URL}`
3. Authenticate with the gateway credentials above
4. Load the preinstalled `LTX-Video` or `Wan 2.1` workflow inside ComfyUI
